mention.text: The awful shadow of some unseen Power

us ; visiting This various world with as inconstant wing As summer winds that creep from flower to flower ; Like moonbeams that behind some piny mountain shower , It visits with inconstant glance Each human heart and countenance ; Like hues and harmonies of evening , Like clouds in starlight widely spread , Like memory of music fled , Like aught that for its grace
summer winds that creep from flower to flower
Spirit of BEAUTY , that dost consecrate With thine own hues all thou dost shine upon Of human thought or form , where art thou gone ?
dost consecrate With thine own hues all thou dost
This dim vast vale of tears
Love , Hope , and Self-esteem , like clouds depart And come , for some uncertain moments lent .
Didst thou , unknown and awful as thou art
wane in lovers ' eyes ; Thou , that to human thought art nourishment , Like darkness
Thou , that to human thought art nourishment
Thou messenger of sympathies , That wax and wane in lovers ' eyes ; Thou , that to human thought art nourishment , Like darkness to a dying flame !
I vow 'd that I would dedicate my powers To thee and thine : have I
the truth Of nature on my passive youth
